<p>
Ethan Jacobson, Senior Software Architect at Nevo,
has developed a profound understanding of the subtle and complex design issues in highly distributed, web-based systems. Before joining Nevo he has built the architecture for MediLife, Inc.'s consumer self-care
applications, led the design and implementation of a database abstraction mechanism for Interleaf, Inc. and contributed to the design of the Atari 7800 ProSystem for General Computer Company. 
</p><p>
Among his projects at Nevo are the design and implementation of the .NET based metadata-driven architecture of the Acushnet OASIS mobile sales automation application, the development of applications for the Registrar's Office and Admissions Office at Harvard University, architecting and implementing a distributed application for Structured Settlements, designing and implementing a number of award winning applications for John Hancock, and most recently, providing a lead role in the development of a distributed application now used by hundreds of residential energy auditors.
</p>
<p>Mr. Jacobson earned a BS degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from Princeton University.

